.SH NAME
CWE\-772 \- Missing Release of Resource after Effective Lifetime
.SH RANK
KEV\-referenced weakness. Not part of the 2025 CWE Top 25; documented here because it appears in the CISA KEV catalog.
.SH CLASSIFICATION
Class: KEV\-referenced weakness.
.SH DESCRIPTION
The product does not release a resource after its effective lifetime has ended, i.e., after the resource is no longer needed. When a resource is not released after use, it can allow attackers to cause a denial of service by causing the allocation of resources without triggering their release. Frequently\-affected resources include memory, CPU, disk space, power or battery, etc.
.SH KNOWN EXPLOITED VULNERABILITIES
